verbose_text: One of the key altered miRNAs was miR-29a, which suppressed the expression of its target gene, peroxisome proliferator activated receptor delta (PPARdelta), and influenced the expressions of other related genes, such as peroxisome proliferator activated receptor-gamma coactivator-1alpha (PGC-1alpha) and glucose transporter 4 (GLUT4), as well as decreasing insulin stimulated glucose uptake and adenosine triphosphate (ATP) production in the skeletal muscle cell line C2C12.
evidence: expression of its target gene, peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor delta
